                <pb n="1"/>
                
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands&#34;<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant and Importer&#44;<lb/>
                PURCHASER OF REAL ESTATE &#40;LANDED PROPERTY&#41;.<lb/>
                A Large Stock of DIAMONDS&#44; Rough and Polished&#44; also PRECIOUS<lb/>
                STONES in every variety&#44; always on hand.<lb/>
                BOX 3927&#44; EQUITABLE SAFE DEPOSIT VAULTS&#44; 67 MILK STREET &#40;directly opposite the Post&#45;Office&#41;.<lb/>
                Residence&#44; 127 DARTMOUTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before<lb/> sunset on Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish<lb/> Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Sivan 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> A. M. 5642.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your&#39;s of some days since<lb/> received &#38; extreme press of business has<lb/> prevented my reply which I hope to<lb/> do so in a few days.  If I am not<lb/> asking too much will you write from<lb/> enclosed circular an article for the<lb/> Record&#44; also send one to the American<lb/> Hebrew.  Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Mr Rabinowitz is a sincere<lb/> &#38; pious man.  My feeling towards him are<lb/> such of the purest affection for his<lb/> zeal &#38; love for our Holy Religion &#38; I<lb/> doubt if his equal is to be found all<lb/> over the world.  He married myself &#38; dear<lb/> wife&#44; circumcised my dear son&#44; &#38; for the<lb/> last twenty years has been my personal<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>friend.  I received a letter today from<lb/> one of the leading &#38; wealthiest Jews at<lb/> Cape Town&#44; he writes of late years<lb/> Mr. Rabinowitz has made progress in<lb/> many ways &#38; has not only succeed in<lb/> saving &#38; earning sufficient means to enable<lb/> him to return but has also attained a good<lb/> position being highly respected not only by the<lb/> members of our Faith but by his fellow<lb/> townsmen of all denominations.<lb/></p>
            <p>Since Mr. Brususan writes me farther<lb/> since the affliction he met with the loss of<lb/> his two sons last Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. he as far as possible<lb/> held <sic>alof</sic> from public business of any nature<lb/> but he felt it is duty to allow his name to be<lb/> put on the Committee so as to assist in some<lb/> measure in paying respect where he feels it is<lb/> justly due.&#34;  &#40;No man all over the world<lb/> has worked more faithful from the Cape of<lb/> Good Hope Mauritius. Rio Janier&#44; &#38; India<lb/> &#38; <del>no</del> remitted more money from persecuted<lb/> brethren in Russia than Mr. Rabinowitz<lb/> with the most kind &#38; sincere regards<lb/> in which Mrs. Marcus daughter &#38; son join<lb/> &#38; remain <sic>your&#39;s</sic> faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            </body>
